title: Match History
body:
I tried checking my match history on the league of legends web page, and when I go to check, the match history page is blank, what to do.

My f5 key doesn't function right, it skips videos, it doesn't refreshes the page.

replies.body:
There are some known issues on that page, but there are some workarounds we can address in order to potentially bypass this issue. Try [**clearing your web browser's cache**](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/201752694-Clearing-Browser-History-and-Cookies) and try **CTRL+F5** for a proper refresh on the page.

Let me know if this caused any change.
it did not, my F5 key does not function, it skips videos only, please help me find a solution Targons Blade.
Gotcha. Does this happen on all web browsers? Try a few different web browsers so we can see if this is caused by a configuration or extension on your browser.
Nope. I'm using a Dell laptop right now, and the F5 function for Dell is to skip a video. That's just how Dell decided to make this laptop. So it's nothing wrong with the browser.
Ah, I didn't mean the F5 function was caused by browser issues, I meant your issue with the blank match history page. Give it a go and let me know if that caused a change.
It happens on both Windows 10 and Chrome, I really don't know what to do at the moment. So how is your day?

My day is going just fine. ^.^

Since you're still having issues with this, I recommend we escalate this to our tech team for further troubleshooting. I'd like you to grab some system logs using our [**HRT App**](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/articles/224826367), then attach the zipped logs to a [**support ticket**](https://support.riotgames.com/hc/en-us/requests/new) so we can get back to you.

Let me know if you have any questions.
Thanks, you have been very helpful. I hope you help others as well! :]
thanks, but my f5 key is programed to skip videos, not refresh tabs. any suggestions on getting it fixed?
It's not working for me either.
